cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper introduces a new Bayesian multi-class support vector machine and employs deep learning components to enable learning for unstructured data. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, given the focus on machine learning and the use of deep learning components, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant due to the use of computer vision and neural networks, as well as the potential applications in social and information networks.
